.TH KONGFIG 1 "2026-03-22" "kongfig" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kongfig \- manage simple configuration values via symbolic links
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kongfig
.br
.B kongfig
.I key
.br
.B kongfig
.I key value
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kongfig
stores configuration entries as symbolic links in a directory tree.

By default, the storage directory is:
.IP
.B $HOME/.kongfig

If the environment variable
.B KONGFIG
is set, that path is used instead.

The command supports three forms:
.TP
.B kongfig
List entries in the configured directory (if it exists).
.TP
.B kongfig 
.I key
Show a single entry for
.IR key .
If the key exists and is a symbolic link, the command prints link details.
.TP
.B kongfig
.I key value
Create or replace
.I key
so it points to
.IR value .

.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I key
Configuration key name. The key must not contain the slash character
.RB ( / ).
.TP
.I value
Configuration value. In this implementation, values are stored as symlink
targets and must not contain
.RB ( / )
when assigned through
.BR kongfig .

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B KONGFIG
Root directory used by the command.
Default: 
.BR $HOME/.kongfig .

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid input (for example, key/value contains slash) or an option-like
argument is passed.

.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
KONGFIG=/tmp/kfg kongfig name "Fred Flintstone"
KONGFIG=/tmp/kfg kongfig name
KONGFIG=/tmp/kfg kongfig
.fi

.SH NOTES
.IP \[bu] 2
The current script prints the selected storage directory as
.B KONGFIG=<path>
on each run.
.IP \[bu] 2
The command does not support option flags such as
.B -k
or
.BR -v .
Those flags belong to the separate
.B kongfigtest
program in this repository.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kongfigtest (1),
.BR ln (1),
.BR readlink (1)
